[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow. The overflow occurs during entity declaration parsing, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspecifically in the function `xmlSBufAddEntitySecure`, when copying data for [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparameter entity expansion. The invalid read of [0m[1;36m48[0m[39m bytes beyond a [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m-byte heap [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation leads to an immediate crash under ASan.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue Manifestation  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  During an interactive fuzzing session [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`run_fuzzer xml -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer reports a multi-byte read overflow in `xmlSBufAddEntitySecure` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mparser.[0m[1;92mc:777[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The crash stack trace shows that the overflow happens when [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`__asan_memcpy` attempts to copy [0m[1;36m48[0m[39m bytes from an [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-bit counter buffer that was [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly allocated for [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m bytes.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability Type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Classified as a heap-buffer-overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39mout-of-bounds read[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. ASan labels it [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“multi-byte-read-heap-buffer-overflow” with a scariness level of [0m[1;36m26[0m[39m.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key Observations  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. The faulty read originates in `xmlSBufAddEntitySecure`, which is called by [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlExpandPEsInEntityValue`.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. The call chain climbs through `xmlParseEntityValue` → `xmlParseEntityDecl` → [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlParseInternalSubset` → `xmlParseDocument` → `xmlCtxtParseDocument`, and finally[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minto the fuzz entrypoint `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. The buffer in question was allocated via `xmlFuzzMalloc` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfuzz.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlStrdup`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`xmlStrndup` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlstring.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, producing a [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m-byte region. Immediately [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafter, `xmlSBufAddEntitySecure` tries to extend or copy more data than the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocated length.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. ASan’s shadow memory indicates the overflow happens right at the boundary of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe allocated heap object, confirming an out-of-bounds read.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Relevant Code Areas for Investigation  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. **xmlSBufAddEntitySecure** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparser.c around line [0m[1;36m777[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m – logic for secure [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentity buffer resizing or copying.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. **xmlExpandPEsInEntityValue** and **xmlParseEntityValue** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparser.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m – how [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentity values are parsed and passed to the buffer routines.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. **Buffer allocation routines** in the fuzz harness and XML string utilities [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`xmlFuzzMalloc`, `xmlStrdup`, `xmlStrndup`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to understand initial buffer sizing.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. **Entity declaration parsing** paths [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`xmlParseEntityDecl`, [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlParseInternalSubset`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to see how input lengths and buffer bounds are computed. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. **Fuzzer harness** entry in `fuzz/xml.c: LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` for how test [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minputs are fed into the parsing pipeline [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthough the harness itself is not the root[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcause[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer run on the xml parser triggered an AddressSanitizer [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow in xmlSBufAddEntitySecure [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparser.[0m[1;92mc:777[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when expanding [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparameter entity values. The attempted patch modified the capacity check in [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlSBufAddEntitySecure to grow the buffer whenever the remaining capacity is [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msmaller than the incoming data length. After applying the patch, the fuzzer still [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreproduces the same heap-buffer-overflow at the same location and call stack, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating the patch did not prevent the out-of-bounds read.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A fuzzing session with libFuzzer and AddressSanitizer on libxml2’s XML parser [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrashes in xmlSBufAddEntitySecure [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparser.[0m[1;92mc:777[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m during entity expansion.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The failure is a multi-byte read past the end of a heap allocation: a [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m-byte [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer is allocated for an entity value, but a [0m[1;36m48[0m[39m-byte memcpy reads beyond that.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Call stack leads from xmlSBufAddEntitySecure through xmlExpandPEsInEntityValue, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlParseEntityValue, xmlParseEntityDecl, xmlParseInternalSubset, and [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlParseDocument, finally hit by the fuzz target LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The sanitizer log shows the redzone bytes and confirms the exact overflow [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboundary [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0x502[0m[33m...[0m[39mb37 is [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes past a [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m-byte region[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In parser.c around line [0m[1;36m766[0m[39m, the original code only grew the string buffer if its[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcapacity [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`buf->cap`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was zero.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch changes the condition to also grow when `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf->cap - buf->size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m < len`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mi.e., the free space is smaller than the data length to add.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Growth is requested via `[0m[1;35mxmlSBufGrow[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf, len * [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After rebuilding with the patched parser.c, repeated fuzzing still trips the same[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer error at parser.[0m[1;92mc:777[0m[39m in xmlSBufAddEntitySecure.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The log before and after the patch shows identical crashing location, same stack [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtrace, and same size of overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39mREAD of size [0m[1;36m48[0m[39m past a [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m-byte region[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The buffer growth logic in xmlSBufAddEntitySecure and the behavior of [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlSBufGrow: whether it actually increases `cap` sufficiently for the requested [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`len`.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The calculation and source of the `len` parameter passed into [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlSBufAddEntitySecure: potentially derived from entity definitions in [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlParseEntityDecl or xmlExpandPEsInEntityValue.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Interactions between the fuzz allocator [0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlFuzzMalloc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, xmlStrdup/xmlStrndup, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand internal entity storage [0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlCreateEntity, xmlAddEntity[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m which set up the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minitial buffers.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The code paths in xmlExpandPEsInEntityValue and xmlParseEntityValue that lead to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrepeated or nested calls to xmlSBufAddEntitySecure.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Any other buffer management functions in parser.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., xmlSAX2EntityDecl[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmight bypass or miscompute buffer capacities.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libxml2 fuzzing run triggered an AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow in [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser.c’s xmlSBufAddEntitySecure while expanding parameter entities. The overflow [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marises from a memcpy reading past an allocated region [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m7[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when handling [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentity values. To address this, a patch was applied to add capacity checks and grow[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoubling the needed size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in xmlSBufAddEntitySecure and [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlSBufAddString. After applying the patch, the compiler emits a flood of “function[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefinition is not allowed here” errors for virtually every subsequent function in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser.c, indicating that the patch disrupted function/block boundaries.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- During fuzzing with libFuzzer, AddressSanitizer reports a heap-buffer-overflow at[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser.[0m[1;92mc:777[0m[39m in xmlSBufAddEntitySecure.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash stack shows: xmlSBufAddEntitySecure → xmlExpandPEsInEntityValue → [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlParseEntityValue → xmlParseEntityDecl → xmlParseInternalSubset → [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlParseDocument → LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The faulty memory was allocated via xmlFuzzMalloc in xmlStrndup for an entity [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstring [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m7[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but a [0m[1;36m48[0m[39m-byte memcpy overruns this region.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- ASAN’s shadow-byte summary and allocation backtrace confirm an out-of-bounds read[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately after the allocated heap block.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Two code blocks in parser.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround lines [0m[1;36m768[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m786[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m were modified. The [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moriginal branches that grew the sbuf when [0m[33mcap[0m[39m==[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m or cap-size<=len were replaced by [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma unified guard:  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf->cap < buf->size + len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      unsigned int need = buf->size + len;  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      unsigned int grow = need * [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m;  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mgrow < len * [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          grow = len * [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m;  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mxmlSBufGrow[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf, grow[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf->code == XML_ERR_OK[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              buf->code = XML_ERR_RESOURCE_LIMIT;  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return;  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The first hunk replaces the `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf->cap == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` branch in [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlSBufAddEntitySecure; the second hunk replaces a later `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf->cap - buf->size [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<= len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in xmlSBufAddString.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Compilation fails with errors like:  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  “function definition is not allowed here” at lines defining xmlSBufAddString, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlSBufAddCString, xmlSBufAddChar, xmlSBufAddReplChar, xmlSBufReportError, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlSBufAddEntity, xmlSBufCleanup, xmlCtxtInitializeLate, xmlParserNsCreate, etc.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A final error notes “function declared in block scope cannot have ‘static’ [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstorage class,” and the build halts with “too many errors emitted.”  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The nature and extent of these errors suggest an unmatched brace or misplaced [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msemicolon/brace in the patched region, causing the parser.c file’s function [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefinitions to appear nested or otherwise syntactically invalid.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for further investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Verify brace matching and block scope around the patched code in [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlSBufAddEntitySecure and xmlSBufAddString.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Inspect surrounding context [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcomment delimiters, preprocessor directives[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensure the new `if` blocks do not swallow closing braces of the function.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Review xmlSBufGrow’s signature and behavior to confirm the intended growth logic [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintegrates cleanly.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Examine other sbuf-related functions [0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlSBufAddCString, xmlSBufAddChar, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensure consistent buffer-growth strategy and proper function boundaries.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Assess the entire parser.c file structure after patch to restore valid C syntax [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore re-evaluating overflow mitigations.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mlibxml2[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpphhfickc[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce xml[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow was detected in libxml2’s parser when [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrunning the XML fuzzer. The overflow occurs in the function [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlSBufAddEntitySecure` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparser.c around line [0m[1;36m777[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, triggered by expanding [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparameter entities during parsing. The patch attempt revised the buffer‐growing [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic in `xmlSBufAddEntitySecure`, replacing two separate checks with a unified [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtest on `buf->cap < buf->size + len` and doubling the required capacity on growth. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the same heap-buffer-overflow is still reported at [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39messentially the same code location, indicating the change did not resolve the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderlying issue.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A fuzzing run with libFuzzer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mengine = libfuzzer, mode = interactive, [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m runs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mon libxml2’s XML parser triggered an AddressSanitizer error:  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  “READ of size [0m[1;36m48[0m[39m at [0m[1;36m0x502[0m[33m...[0m[39mb37” in `xmlSBufAddEntitySecure` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`parser.[0m[1;92mc:777[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow is a multi-byte read beyond a [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m‐byte heap allocation, allocated via [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlFuzzMalloc` → `xmlStrdup` → `xmlCreateEntity` → `xmlAddEntity` → [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlSAX2EntityDecl` → `xmlParseEntityDecl` → … → `xmlCtxtParseDocument` → [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Shadow bytes show the access is exactly [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes past the redzone of a [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m‐byte [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregion. The memcpy interceptor in AddressSanitizer catches it.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant observations  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The buggy code had two checks: one for `buf->cap == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m` growing by `len * [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m`, and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mone for `buf->cap - buf->size <= len` growing by `len`. Both conditions could leave[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`buf->cap` too small for the forthcoming memcpy.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow consistently occurs in `xmlSBufAddEntitySecure` during processing of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man entity value, as part of parameter‐entity expansion [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`xmlExpandPEsInEntityValue`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `parser.c` around the beginning of `xmlSBufAddEntitySecure`, the developer [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreplaced both original conditionals with a single check:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf->cap < buf->size + len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      unsigned int need = buf->size + len;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      unsigned int grow = need * [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mgrow < len * [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          grow = len * [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mxmlSBufGrow[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf, grow[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf->code == XML_ERR_OK[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              buf->code = XML_ERR_RESOURCE_LIMIT;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A similar replacement was made for the second growth site later in the same [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After rebuilding and rerunning the fuzzer under the same conditions, [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer still reports a heap-buffer-overflow at `parser.[0m[1;92mc:783[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madjusted line number[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The failing trace and heap layout remain qualitatively [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentical to the initial run.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPost-patch log highlights  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The seed changed but the crash stack is the same: overflow in `__asan_memcpy` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalled by `xmlSBufAddEntitySecure` during entity expansion.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The allocation site and size [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m7[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remain unchanged, and the attempted memcpy[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstill exceeds the buffer region.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for further investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The growth logic in `xmlSBufAddEntitySecure`: how `len` is computed, and whether [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoubling `need` always produces sufficient capacity.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The implementations of `xmlSBufGrow` and underlying buffer allocation to verify [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthey honor requested sizes and update `buf->cap` correctly.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The upstream calls to `xmlSBufAddEntitySecure` in `xmlExpandPEsInEntityValue` and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlParseEntityValue` to understand how entity values and their lengths are passed.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The handling of parameter entities and internal subsets in [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlParseEntityDecl`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`xmlParseInternalSubset` to see if any value truncation or [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmiscalculation of `len` occurs before buffer writes.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzz harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fuzz/xml.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m entry point to confirm no preconditions are [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39massumed by the parser code that the fuzzer violates, leading to unexpected `len` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalues.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[33mFUZZER[0m[39m=[0m[35mxml[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* At least double the added length to avoid thrashing *[0m[35m/[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mgrow < len * [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            grow = len * [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Honor the resource limit *[0m[35m/[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mgrow > buf->max - buf->size[0m[1;39m)[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            grow = buf->max - buf->size;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mxmlSBufGrow[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf, grow[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m [0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Patch [0m[33mResult[0m[39m===[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[33mFUZZER[0m[39m=[0m[35mxml[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpphhfickc[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce xml[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is an AddressSanitizer–reported heap-buffer-overflow in libxml2’s[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser.c, specifically in the function `xmlSBufAddEntitySecure`. A fuzzing run with[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibFuzzer and AddressSanitizer triggers a [0m[1;36m48[0m[39m-byte out-of-bounds read immediately [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafter a [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m-byte allocation. The patch attempt modified two capacity checks in [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlSBufAddEntitySecure` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround lines [0m[1;36m766[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m777[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m786[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m793[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to ensure `buf->cap` is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat least `buf->size + len`, doubling the needed capacity when growing the buffer. [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the same overflow error recurs at the updated line in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlSBufAddEntitySecure`, indicating the buffer‐growth checks did not prevent the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A fuzzing session with libFuzzer on the XML parser triggered an [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer error.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The error stack trace begins with `__asan_memcpy` called from [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlSBufAddEntitySecure` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparser.[0m[1;92mc:777[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and propagates through [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlExpandPEsInEntityValue`, `xmlParseEntityValue`, and `xmlParseEntityDecl`.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - ASan reports a [0m[1;36m48[0m[39m-byte read at address `[0m[1;36m0x502000000b37[0m[39m`, which lies exactly [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes beyond the allocated [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m-byte heap region [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x502000000b30[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x502000000b37[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The small allocation originates from `malloc` via `xmlFuzzMalloc` → [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlStrndup` → `xmlCreateEntity` → `xmlAddEntity` → SAX2 and parser entry points.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Important Observations  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow occurs in a memcpy in `xmlSBufAddEntitySecure`.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The local buffer object `buf` has `cap == [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m` and `size == [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m`, and the code [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempts to append `len == [0m[1;36m48[0m[39m` bytes without sufficient reallocation.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Two separate `if` conditions guarded growth, but both were insufficient to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreempt the overflow.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - File modified: `parser.c` around function `xmlSBufAddEntitySecure`.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Original code had two checks:  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf->cap == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mxmlSBufGrow[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf, len * [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     …[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf->cap - buf->size <= len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mxmlSBufGrow[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf, len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - New code unified the logic to:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Ensure sufficient capacity for the new data *[0m[35m/[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf->cap < buf->size + len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         unsigned int need = buf->size + len;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         unsigned int grow = need * [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mgrow < len * [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             grow = len * [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mxmlSBufGrow[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf, grow[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Applied twice [0m[1;39m([0m[39monce for the initial [0m[33mcap[0m[39m==[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m case and once for the cap-size [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcase[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Result After Patch  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patched build was fuzz-tested under the same parameters [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`-[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The ASan report shows the same heap-buffer-overflow at `parser.[0m[1;92mc:780[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrelocated memcpy[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, with identical allocation size and overflow size.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No change in behavior indicates the new guard conditions did not cover the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath that leads to the overflow, or the requested growth size is still too small in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msome code paths.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The implementation of `xmlSBufGrow` and how it sets or updates `buf->cap`.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All call sites of `xmlSBufAddEntitySecure`, especially how `len` is computed [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand whether it can exceed expected bounds.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Related buffer-management routines in parser.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`xmlSBufAdd`, other sbuf [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctions[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and their interaction with entity expansion.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The XML entity parsing logic in `xmlExpandPEsInEntityValue` and [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlParseEntityValue`, to understand the maximum possible length [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`len`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m passed to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlSBufAddEntitySecure`.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
